        "title": "Harden Workboard modal and drawer accessibility",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Adds Workboard modal and drawer focus lifecycle handling for initial focus, Tab containment, Escape close, and opener focus restore.\n- Marks Workboard background content inert and aria-hidden while a Workboard dialog layer is open.\n- Adds focused Workboard view regressions for modal and drawer keyboard accessibility.\n\n## Verification\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts\n- OPENCLAW_OXLINT_SKIP_PREPARE=1 node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json ui/src/ui/views/workboard.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts\n- pnpm tsgo:test:ui\n- pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 ui/src/ui/views/workboard.ts ui/src/styles/workboard.css ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts\n- git diff --check\n- Browser smoke: Vite at http://127.0.0.1:5177 mounted the real Workboard module in Chromium and verified dialog role/name, initial focus, inert background, Tab containment, and Escape focus return.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Workboard card modal and detail drawer keep keyboard focus inside, close on Escape, return focus to the launcher, and expose useful dialog labels/descriptions.\nReal environment tested: Local Vite Control UI dev server at http://127.0.0.1:5177 with Chromium Playwright against the real Workboard module.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Browser smoke mounted seeded Workboard state, opened the New card modal and detail drawer, queried dialogs by role/name, pressed Tab and Escape, and checked activeElement plus inert and aria-hidden state.\nEvidence after fix: Browser smoke passed; focused Vitest passed 27 Workboard view tests.\nObserved result after fix: Modal focused the title input, drawer focused the dialog, background had inert and aria-hidden while open, Tab stayed in the drawer, and Escape restored focus to the opener.\nWhat was not tested: Full gateway-backed Workboard data flow and screen-reader audio output.",
